

Hypervisor:
    Its a virtual machine monitor or VMM. A software the creates and runs VMs.
    Hypervisor allows 1 host computer to support multiple guest VMs by virtually sharing CPU, memory etc.
    It interacts with kernel.

    Types:
    Type 1(Baremetal):
        hardware -> hypervisor -> guest os

    Type 2(Hosted):
        hardware -> Host OS -> hypervisor -> guest os


VMs vs Containers:
    Containers run on host OS while VMs have their own OS and subsequently its own kernel.

